data.enText: of building
to fall down or fall in suddenly, often after breaking apart

data.chText: 房顶在雪的重压下突然坍塌下来。
data.enText: The roof collapsed under the weight of snow.
of sick person

data.chText: （尤指因病重而）倒下，昏倒，晕倒
data.enText: to fall down (and usually become unconscious), especially because you are very ill/sick

data.chText: 他昏倒在大街上，两小时后便去世了。
data.enText: He collapsed in the street and died two hours later.
relax

data.chText: （尤指工作劳累后）坐下，躺下放松
data.enText: to sit or lie down and relax, especially after working hard

data.chText: 回到家时，我喜欢倒在沙发上听音乐。
data.enText: When I get home I like to collapse on the sofa and listen to music.
fail
to fail suddenly or completely

data.chText: 资方与工会的谈判已告破裂。
data.enText: Talks between management and unions have collapsed.

data.chText: 所有反对此计划的力量均已消除。
data.enText: All opposition to the plan has collapsed.
of prices/currencies
to decrease suddenly in amount or value

data.chText: 在交易数额不佳的消息公布后，股票价格暴跌。
data.enText: Share prices collapsed after news of poor trading figures.
fold

data.chText: 折叠；套缩；可折叠（或套缩）
data.enText: to fold sth into a shape that uses less space; to be able to be folded in this way

data.chText: 这桌子可折叠起来方便存放。
data.enText: The table collapses for easy storage.
medical
if a lung or blood vessel collapses or is collapsed , it falls in and becomes flat and empty
collapsed buildings
a collapsed investment bank
a collapsed lung
failure

data.chText: 突然失败，倒闭，崩溃（如机构、生意或行动的）
data.enText: a sudden failure of sth, such as an institution, a business or a course of action
the collapse of law and order in the area
The peace talks were on the verge of collapse .
of building
the action of a building suddenly falling
The walls were strengthened to protect them from collapse.
illness

data.chText: 病倒；（因病或体弱的）昏倒，晕倒
data.enText: a medical condition when a person suddenly becomes very ill/sick, or when sb falls because they are ill/sick or weak

data.chText: 精神 / 神经的崩溃状态
data.enText: a state of mental/nervous collapse

data.chText: 她在工作时晕倒后被送进了医院。
data.enText: She was taken to hospital after her collapse at work.
of prices/currencies

data.chText: 突然降价；突然贬值；暴跌
data.enText: a sudden fall in value

data.chText: 股票价格 / 美元 / 市场价格暴跌
data.enText: the collapse of share prices/the dollar/the market

simple_means.memory_skill: col 共同 + laps 滑，滑走 + e → 一起滑落 → 倒塌

means: 突然失败(如机构、生意或行动的)

ex.chText: 房顶在雪的重压下突然坍塌了。
ex.enText: The roof collapsed under the weight of snow.

ex.chText: 许多高楼在地震中倒塌了。
ex.enText: A lot of tall buildings collapsed in the earthquake.

synonyms.bx: 通常指房屋等倒塌，强调突然性。

ex.chText: 许多房子坍塌，成了废墟。

ex.enText: The old stone wall began to crumble.
The cliff has gradually crumbled away.

synonyms.bx: 尤指由石头或岩石构成的建筑物或土地崩塌或崩裂。

ex.chText: 在那场暴风雨中，许多树都被刮倒了。
ex.enText: Many trees fell in the storm.

ex.chText: 倒塌的墙壁弄了他们一身土。
ex.enText: The falling wall showered dust on them.

ex.chText: 我跌了一跤，摔伤了膝盖。
ex.enText: I fell and hurt my knee.

synonyms.bx: 通常指因失去平衡等而倒塌或跌倒。

ex.chText: 少了他肩膀的支撑，她倒在地板上。
ex.enText: She sank to the floor without the support of his shoulder.
He was stunned and sank to the ground.

ex.chText: 她筋疲力尽地倒在椅子里。
ex.enText: She sank into a chair, exhausted.

synonyms.bx: 尤指人因过于劳累、体弱等而倒下或坐下。

tr: the act of throwing yourself down
example: he landed on the bed with a great flop

tr: a natural event caused by something suddenly falling down or caving in
example: the roof is in danger of collapse
the collapse of the old star under its own gravity

tr: a sudden large decline of business or the prices of stocks (especially one that causes additional failures)
an abrupt failure of function or complete physical exhaustion
example: the commander's prostration demoralized his men

tr: collapse due to fatigue, an illness, or a sudden attack

example: The roof finally gave under the weight of the ice
the building crumbled after the explosion

value.def: If a building or other structure collapses, it falls down very suddenly.

example.ex: A section of the Bay Bridge had collapsed...
example.tran: 海湾大桥有一段垮塌了。

example.ex: The roof collapsed in a roar of rock and rubble...
example.tran: 屋顶轰隆一声塌了下来，碎石瓦砾落了一地。

example.ex: Most of the deaths were caused by landslides and collapsing buildings.
example.tran: 大部分死亡是由山体滑坡和建筑倒塌造成的。

example.ex: Governor Deukmejian called for an inquiry into the freeway's collapse.
example.tran: 德克梅吉恩州长要求对高速公路塌陷事件进行调查。

value.def: If something, for example a system or institution, collapses, it fails or comes to an end completely and suddenly.

example.ex: His business empire collapsed under a massive burden of debt...
example.tran: 他的商业帝国无力承担沉重的债务负担而垮掉了。

example.ex: This system has collapsed in most countries where it ruled...
example.tran: 这一体系在其占统治地位的大多数国家都失败了。

example.ex: The rural people have been impoverished by a collapsing economy.
example.tran: 经济崩溃使农村地区的人们一贫如洗。

example.ex: The coup's collapse has speeded up the drive to independence...
example.tran: 政变失败加速了独立运动的进程。

example.ex: Their economy is teetering on the brink of collapse.
example.tran: 他们的经济岌岌可危，正处在崩溃的边缘。

value.tran: (体系或机构)崩溃，瓦解，突然失败

value.def: If you collapse, you suddenly faint or fall down because you are very ill or weak.

example.ex: He collapsed following a vigorous exercise session at his home...
example.tran: 在家剧烈运动了一阵后他突然昏倒了。

example.ex: It's commonplace to see people collapsing from hunger in the streets.
example.tran: 在街上看见有人饿晕是很平常的事。

example.ex: A few days after his collapse he was sitting up in bed.
example.tran: 他病倒后没过几天就又能在床上坐起来了。

value.tran: (因生病或虚弱)突然倒下，昏倒

value.def: If you collapse onto something, you sit or lie down suddenly because you are very tired.

example.ex: She arrived home exhausted and barely capable of showering before collapsing on her bed.
example.tran: 她精疲力竭地回到家，勉强冲了个澡就倒在了床上。

value.tran: (因精疲力竭而)突然坐下(或倒下)

value.def: If something with air inside collapses, it falls inwards and becomes smaller or flatter.

example.ex: He plunged 300ft to the ground when his parachute collapsed...
example.tran: 降落伞突然瘪了，他从300英尺的高空跌落到地面。

example.ex: He was rushed to hospital last week after suffering a collapsed lung.
example.tran: 上星期，他因出现肺萎陷而被火速送进医院。

trans: 破坏机构；极限荷载只需分析破坏机构；崩塌机构
破坏（临界纵向）负荷；破坏（极限）荷载

partsOfSpeech.dec: col 共同 + laps 滑，滑走 + e → 一起滑落 → 倒塌
e 加强 + laps 滑，滑走 + e → 滑走 →〔时光〕流逝
laps 滑，滑走 + e → 堕落；犯错误
laps 滑，滑走 + ed 表形容词 → 从潮流中溜过 → 过时的
re 重新 + laps 滑，滑走 + e → 重新滑落 →〔病〕复发
